ish domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert d’Aubigny I was born about 1130, in Clophill, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Henry d'Aubigny, was 37 and his mother, Cecily Chaworth, was 23. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1191, in Clophill, Bedfordshire, England, at the age of 62."},"et":{"about 1130–1191":"umbes 1130–1191","1130–1191":"1130–1191","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1095–1130":"1095–1130","1109–Female":"1109–Surnud","Abt 1130":"umbes 1130","1221":"1221","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","1150":"1150","about 1130":"umbes 1130","1109":"1109","1191":"1191","Cainhoe Castle, Clophill, Bedfordshire, England":"Clophill, Bedfordshire, England","Cainhoe Castle, Clophill, Central Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Clophill, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1130–1191":"noin 1130–1191","1130–1191":"1130–1191","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1095–1130":"1095–1130","1109–Female":"1109–Kuollut","Abt 1130":"noin 1130","1221":"1221","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","1150":"1150","about 1130":"noin 1130","1109":"1109","1191":"1191","Cainhoe Castle, Clophill, Bedfordshire, England":"Clophill, Bedfordshire, England","Cainhoe Castle, Clophill, Central Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Clophill, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1130–1191":"environ 1130–1191","1130–1191":"1130–1191","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1095–1130":"1095–1130","1109–Female":"1109–Décédée","Abt 1130":"environ 1130","1221":"1221","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","1150":"1150","about 1130":"environ 1130","1109":"1109","1191":"1191","Cainhoe Castle, Clophill, Bedfordshire, England":"Clophill, Bedfordshire, Angleterre","Cainhoe Castle, Clophill, Central Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Clophill, Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Rober